	<element name="Godly Empowerment" type="Archetype Feature" source="Subclasses Galore" id="ID_SUB_GALORE_ARCHETYPE_FEATURE_DEITY_GODLY_EMPOWERMENT">
		<description>
			<p>Starting at 1st level,once per short rest you ask your patron to empower your spells adding damage equal to your Charisma modifier + your warlock level (minimum of 1).</p>
		</description>
		<sheet>
			<description usage="1/Short Rest">You ask your patron tp empower your spells adding {{godly damage:temp hp}} damage.</description>
		</sheet>
		<rules>
			<stat name="godly damage:damage" value="charisma:modifier" />
			<stat name="godly damage:damage" value="level:warlock" />
		</rules>
	</element>
	<element name="Godly Benefector" type="Archetype Feature" source="Subclasses Galore" id="ID_SUB_GALORE_ARCHETYPE_FEATURE_DEITY_BENEFACTOR">
		<description>
			<p>Starting at 6th level, you can call on your patron to alter fate in your favor. When you make an ability check or a saving throw, you can use this feature to add a d10 to your roll. You can do so after seeing the initial roll but before any of the roll’s effects occur.</p>
			<p class="indent">Once you use this feature, you can’t use it again until you finish a short or long rest.</p>
		</description>
		<sheet usage="1/Short Rest">
			<description>When you make an ability check or a saving throw, you can use this feature to add a d10 to your roll.</description>
		</sheet>
	</element>
	<element name="Godly Resilience" type="Archetype Feature" source="Subclasses Galore" id="ID_SUB_GALORE_ARCHETYPE_FEATURE_DEITY_GODLY_RESILIENCE">
		<description>
			<p>Starting at 10th level, you are resistant to one type of damage decided by your domain.</p>
			<table>
				<thead>
					<tr><td>Divine Domain</td><td>Resistance</td></tr>
				</thead>
				<tr><td>Plague</td><td><i>Poison</i></td></tr>
				<tr><td>Knowledge</td><td><i>Psychic</i></td></tr>
				<tr><td>Life</td><td><i>Radiant</i></td></tr>
				<tr><td>Nature</td><td><i>Acid</i></td></tr>
				<tr><td>Light</td><td><i>Radiant</i></td></tr>
                <tr><td>Tempest</td><td><i>Thunder</i></td></tr>
                <tr><td>Trickery</td><td><i>Psychic</i></td></tr>
                <tr><td>War</td><td><i>Bludgeoning</i></td></tr>
			</table>
		</description>
		<sheet>
			<description> You gain resistance to that damage type chosen by your domain </description>
		</sheet>
	</element>
	<element name="Divine Unleashment" type="Archetype Feature" source="Subclasses Galore" id="ID_SUB_GALORE_ARCHETYPE_FEATURE_DEITY_DIVINE_ENERGY">
		<description>
			<p>Starting at 14th level, when you hit a foe with an attack, you can use this feature to instantly unleash divine energy from your patron into your foe</p>
			<p class="indent">If the target fails a DC15 Constitution save, it takes 6d10 Radiant damage, on a success take half.</p>
			<p class="indent">Once you use this feature, you can’t use it again until you finish a long rest.</p>
			<p class ="indent">You also must succeed a DC13 Consitution save or take 1d12 Radiant Damage from the energy through you </p>
		</description>
		<sheet usage="1/Long Rest">
			<description>When you hit a foe with an attack, you can use this feature to instantly unleash divine energy from your patron into your foe, causing a DC15 CON save, doing 6d10 Radiant Damage on a Failure or half on a success, while you have a DC12 CON Save or take 1d12 Radiant Damage</description>
		</sheet>
	</element>
